01:06:15,000 --> 01:06:16,020
I think it was for radius.

1949
01:06:16,020 --> 01:06:17,740
But for now,

1950
01:06:17,740 --> 01:06:18,280
it stands

1951
01:06:18,280 --> 01:06:20,040
for the position of the particle.

1952
01:06:20,040 --> 01:06:22,160
What are the components of r?

1953
01:06:24,360 --> 01:06:25,360
They're just the x,

1954
01:06:25,360 --> 01:06:25,580
y,

1955
01:06:25,580 --> 01:06:26,640
and z of the particle.

1956
01:06:26,640 --> 01:06:28,840
They're just the coordinates of the particle

1957
01:06:28,840 --> 01:06:29,120
x,

1958
01:06:29,120 --> 01:06:29,340
y,

1959
01:06:29,340 --> 01:06:29,660
and z.

1960
01:06:29,660 --> 01:06:33,340
So r has coordinates x,

1961
01:06:33,340 --> 01:06:33,560
y,

1962
01:06:33,560 --> 01:06:33,980
and z.

1963
01:06:33,980 --> 01:06:36,000
Or let me not write it that way.

1964
01:06:36,000 --> 01:06:37,660
r sub x

1965
01:06:39,880 --> 01:06:41,120
is equal to x,

1966
01:06:41,120 --> 01:06:42,300
the position x,

1967
01:06:42,300 --> 01:06:43,700
and so forth and so on.

1968
01:06:43,700 --> 01:06:46,140
That's the notion,

1969
01:06:46,140 --> 01:06:47,100
the simple notion

1970
01:06:47,100 --> 01:06:51,520
of the location of a particle described as a vector.

1971
01:06:55,220 --> 01:06:55,780
Now,

1972
01:06:55,780 --> 01:06:56,800
in general,

1973
01:06:56,800 --> 01:07:00,180
we are interested in the motion of particles.

1974
01:07:00,180 --> 01:07:02,420
The motion of particles

1975
01:07:03,100 --> 01:07:05,560
is what classical mechanics is about.

1976
01:07:05,560 --> 01:07:09,200
How the motion goes from one instant to the next.

1977
01:07:09,400 --> 01:07:09,800
In other words,

1978
01:07:09,800 --> 01:07:11,880
how it's updated from one instant to the next.

1979
01:07:11,880 --> 01:07:13,420
And so we should think

1980
01:07:13,420 --> 01:07:16,100
about r as a function of time in general.

1981
01:07:16,100 --> 01:07:18,740
It moves around,

1982
01:07:18,740 --> 01:07:20,940
however it moves around.

1983
01:07:21,180 --> 01:07:22,140
We'll assume it moves around.

1984
01:07:22,140 --> 01:07:22,140
We'll assume it moves around.

1985
01:07:22,140 --> 01:07:22,140
We'll assume it moves around.

1986
01:07:22,160 --> 01:07:23,300
It moves around continuously,

1987
01:07:23,300 --> 01:07:24,880
differentially,

1988
01:07:24,880 --> 01:07:26,260
smoothly.

1989
01:07:26,260 --> 01:07:29,320
And at the same time,

1990
01:07:29,320 --> 01:07:30,000
it's components.

1991
01:07:30,900 --> 01:07:32,900
If r is a function of time,

1992
01:07:32,900 --> 01:07:37,180
then r sub x is also a function of time,

1993
01:07:37,180 --> 01:07:39,500
likewise for y of

1994
01:07:40,120 --> 01:07:42,040
t and z of t.

1995
01:07:42,040 --> 01:07:46,480
And so the motion of a particle is summarized,

1996
01:07:46,480 --> 01:07:47,180
in this case,

1997
01:07:47,180 --> 01:07:48,340
by three functions

1998
01:07:48,340 --> 01:07:49,000
